All Classes

Class Description
AI
The AI is used to add new words to the board when the player selects single payer.
AppContainer
The AppContainer class contains the GUI game board, the players' point display, and the buttons used to place tiles on the GUI game board and end the current turn.
Colors
This interface defines the Color constants used for the backgrounds and foregrounds of components in the game's GUI.
Difficulty
The Difficulty constants representing the different difficulty settings of the game.
GameBoard
The GameBoard class sets up the game board(not GameBoardGUI).
GameState
The GameState class is an aggregate of all classes that comprise the "state" of the application.
LoadGameMenuPanel
The LoadGameMenuPanel is the GUI where players are able to choose which save game state/slot to load up.
MainView
The MainView class is the GUI window that displays the menu and game board of the game.
MenuBar
The MenuBar class is a menu bar which allow players to access certain menus such as load game, save game, settings, or rules.
MenuPanel
MenuPanel sets up the main "panel" which holds the different menus of the program-- Start Menu, Options Menu, Load Game Menu, etc.
NavigationListener
The NavigationListener is an Action Listener class used by any buttons in the GUI that cause a new menu or screen to be loaded into the GUI window of the application.
Node
This is the Node class and it will store all the information need in one block on the board.
OptionsMenuPanel
The OptionsMenuPanel contains GUI components that allow the user to modify the settings of the application (toggling tutorial tooltips and setting difficulty to on or off).
Player  
Player  
RulesPanel
The RulesPanel class makes the GUI that displays the Rules to Players.
SaveGameMenuPanel
SaveGameMenuPanel is the GUI window where players are able to save their current game into any of the four save slots.
ScrabbleTrie
The ScrabbleTrie is a tree-like structure that emulates a Scrabble dictionary.
ScrabbleTrie.TrieNode
The TrieNode represents a node within the ScrabbleTrie trie/tree structure.
ScrabbleTrieDriver  
SelectGameModePanel
The SelectGameModePanel is the GUI that allow player(s) to choose which gamemode to play: Single-Player or Multi-player
SelectPlayersMenuPanel
The SelectPlayersMenuPanel is the GUI window that allows player to choose how many players and enter players' names.
StartMenuPanel
The JPanel-derived GUI container class containing the Start Menu.
Stuff  
Tile
The Tile class represents a Scrabble Tile.
TileBag  
TileBag  
TilePlacement
The TilePlacement class represents a Scrabble tile along with its position on the game board.
WordChecker
The WordChecker is used to verify that the tiles placed on the scrabble board gui by the player during their turn form one or more valid words according to the rules of Scrabble.
WordCheckerDriver  
WordScoreCalculator
